# Fill a mode-0600 copy, import it with `yard keys`, and materialize `qa-secrets`.
# `yard qa-pool up` stages the generated consumer
# ro into the yard and registers the two values as Convex DEPLOYMENT env vars (via `convex env
# set`, NOT container -e — Convex functions read them from the deployment env store). The broker
# checks the Authorization: Bearer <secret> against these:
#   - MAINTAINER secret: admin/* (add/remove/list) AND acquire/heartbeat/release.
#   - CI secret:         acquire/heartbeat/release only (what a dev-agent worker uses).
# Seeding the pool uses MAINTAINER; the exposed worker env (yard qa-pool expose) carries CI.
#
# Generate strong distinct values, e.g.:  openssl rand -hex 32

# Required. Used to seed the pool (admin/add) and for maintainer-role leases.
OPENCLAW_QA_CONVEX_SECRET_MAINTAINER=

# Required. Handed to dev-agent workers (the CI-role token for --credential-source convex).
OPENCLAW_QA_CONVEX_SECRET_CI=

# Optional. The Convex backend's instance secret (the admin key is derived from it). Leave empty
# to have `up` generate one and persist it in the yard's broker data root (re-used across
# container recreate). Set it here only if you want a fixed value across full yard rebuilds.
#   CONVEX_INSTANCE_SECRET=
